column5: Hey, anyone hit the Grand River for browns yet ?  Thinking of throwing some flies this week.  Thanks, Nuke
Went to Elora last night, water is clear but really high and fast. Best to give it a week or so.
Thanks Marko.  Were you by the train trussle ?  I usually hunt browns in Fergus.  I thought the water level would have gone down by now. I'll wait a week.  Thanks again, Nuke
I ended up at the  conservation area in Elora. I usually fish there bellow the mill, havent tried  Fergus yet.
hey  i live in Caledonia and i have been gettin a few

Just chuck some giant streamers around when the water is flowin too high........but sometimes too high is just too high!!  I drove by yesterday and the water was probably up a foot to a foot and a half.  we went to the other place
